==English==
===Interjection===
'''[[shut]] [[up]]'''

# ([[Informal]]) {{idiom}} Said to people to stop them talking or making noise. Generally used to insult, to command attention, or to convey urgency, but is sometimes used lightheartedly by teens or among close friends.
#:''Would you please '''shut up''' about it?  Screaming won't help.'' 

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[ole hiljaa]] / [[olkaa hiljaa]], [[hiljaa]]
*Japanese: [[だまれ]] (damare)
*Norwegian: [[hold kjeft]], [[hold tåta]], [[kjeft´n]] 
*Spanish: [[callate]]
*Portuguese: [[Cala a boca]]
*Swedish: [[håll tyst]], [[håll käften]]
*German: [[Halt den Mund]]
*Italian: [[Taci]]

===Usage note===
This expression is typically used in the imperative, and may be considered forceful or inconsiderate.  

[[sv:shut up]]